name: The Custodian print
description:
This is the print version of an original work of mine that won the 2013 Spring St Paul Art Crawl poster competition, which was originally created for a show supporting the custodial and security officers union which was on strike early in 2013, and of which I was once a member. I am very proud to have this work as a permanent part of St Paul's art history.

The print measures 18 x 24 inches, is 4 colors, is on 100 lb poptone paper from French Paper Co, and is from a signed and numbered edition of only 50 prints.

Print will be shipped carefully rolled in a heavy duty mailing tube within 5 business days of receiving your order.

Enjoy!

name: Summit Brewing Co. Pilsener limited edition screenprinted poster
description:
This is a print I was very excited to be hired to create. Advertising Saint Paul's own Summit Brewing Co.'s Pilsener beer. The barley used to make the beer is grown on a family farm in North Dakota.

THIS IS NOT A DIGITAL PRINT.


Entirely hand drawn and manually printed, the print measures 18 x 24 inches, is 4 colors on 100 lb whipcream poptone paper from Mr French Paper Co, and comes from a signed and numbered AP edition of only 60 prints.

Print will be shipped carefully rolled in a heavy duty mailing tube within 5 business days of receiving your order. 

Enjoy!

name: Portraits Volume One book
description:
I am proud to present the first hardbound book collecting my art. I owe its existence to all of my Kickstarter backers, who supported me in the infancy of this project.

 'Portraits Volume One' collects the work I've done over the last 5 years on my ongoing 'Portraits' series, which features a wide range of strange faces drawn in a variety of styles. Some sample pages are available for view to the left.

   The book is 104 pages, and has 100 pages of full color art. The book is printed offset, not digitally, and is hardbound. The pages measure 6 x 9 inches. The first edition is only 500, and of that only 400 are available (the first 100 are going to my Kickstarter backers)

The book will be shipped in a sturdy envelope within 5 business days of receiving your order.

Thank you & Enjoy!

name: The Next Round art print
description:
This is a 9 color print I made up as I went. I didn't start with any idea what I was going to do, just the title had been settled on. It has all of my favorite aspects of a print: layers & layers of ink, transparencies, bright colors, split fountains, and happy accidents.

  It measures 18 x 24 inches, is on 80 lb orange butcher paper from French Paper Co, and is from a signed and numbered edition of only 25 prints.

Print will be shipped carefully rolled in a heavy duty mailing tube within 5 business days of receiving your order.

name: Universe Cruiser art print
description:
This is a benchmark print for both me and the ever-expanding Artcrank bicycle themed poster events. Currently the record holder for any Artcrank show, this print has a whopping 16 colors, also the most I have ever planned out for a print. It even has a spot gloss varnish for extra 'Pop!' in person. It took me an entire week to print it.

THIS IS NOT A DIGITAL PRINT.

  Entirely hand drawn and manually printed, it is titled 'Universe Cruiser', and is 18 x 24 inches on 100 lb razzleberry blue poptone paper from French Paper Company.  As I mentioned, it is 16 colors, and comes from a signed and numbered edition of only 70 prints.

  The print will be carefully rolled and shipped in a heavy duty mailing tube within 5 business days of receiving your order.

Enjoy!
